<br>
Once you get to the PoP levels, groups are very dependant on slowers and CHealers.  So, they don't really have a hard time finding groups.  But, if you have the tanks as your friends, you might get an in.<br>
<br>
You can also try being door bitc....errr...opener in CoM to make friends with Rangers and Druids trying to get their epics.  That way when you are LFG in PoV for 3 hours at level 62 and you see them soloing there.  You can always work the guilt trip on helping them get their epic so you can become their kiting &quot;pet&quot;.<br>
<br>
Just a few thoughts from the forever LFG rogue of 65 seasons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vicairedelestacia@firionavie>Vicaire Delestacia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 10:01:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4167.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> You know, I hear a lot about rogues having lfg problems, but I have only ever seen it once.  About two months ago I saw three mid 50s rogues lfg at once.  Ever since then I never see more than one lfg, and that one not for long, and trying to form my dream group of three rogues included just doesn't happen much less forming a trials group with them.  <br>
